ng on your state you might not need a motorcycle endorsement on your license a majority of states are now classifying the slingshot® as an autocycle allowing you to drive one with only a valid driver’s license check your state operator laws to see what is required in your state helmet laws vary from state to state and are dependent on slingshot® classification slingshot® recommends always wearing a dot approved full face helmet learn more license requirements the slingshot® openair roadster is classified as an autocycle in many states where the driver is only required to have a valid driver’s license learn more apparel  accessories stand out from the standouts with slingshot® engineered accessories  apparel shop now stay connected to the road and everything else escape the ordinary while staying in touch introducing slingshot® ride command® learn more street feed × sign up for exclusive slingshot email offers  updates privacy policy legal notice all fields required do you have your motorcycle license select answer yes no do you currently own any power sports vehicles or motorcycles select answer yes no when do you plan to acquire a slingshot select answer less than  months  months  months greater than a year no definite plans submit top sportsman atvs  quads   wheelers  polaris offroad vehicles sportsman® atvs  quads hardest working smoothest riding the most refined ride unstoppable performance towing and load capacity build your own get internet price special offers   best selling sportsman® just got better the  sportsman®  is back and better than ever packed with durability upgrades and other new features the  continues to be the best value atv on the market  see details trade in trade up time to upgrade your ride estimate your tradein recutility best selling automatic x ever recutility sportutility the most powerful sportsman® sportutility up  utility share the offroad experience up  utility mud  sport purpose built high performance mud  sport industrys best sell