lity use our product lines consist of our polaris ranger® rzr® and polaris general™ sidebyside offroad vehicles our sportsman® and polaris ace® allterrainoffroad vehicles victory® and indian motorcycle® midsize and heavyweight motorcycles slingshot® motoroadsters and polaris rmk® indy® switchback® and rush® snowmobiles polaris enhances the riding experience with parts garments and accessories sold under multiple recognizable brands and has a growing presence in adjacent markets globally with products including military and commercial offroad vehicles quadricycles and electric vehicles a fresh management mix since  weve added new management to complement polaris proven design and manufacturing expertise more than half our top managers are new to the company bringing new ideas and worldclass experience in vital areas such as international business marketing retail merchandising and distribution  quality we unveiled an action plan in  to increase cost performance through ongoing quality initiatives quality enhancements included a new product development process failure mode and effects analysis fmea for manufacturing and a new production part approval process to help us maintain the highestquality supplier partnerships  employee ownership our nonunion workforce is compensated based on company performance through generous profitsharing and stockoption plans all employees own polaris stock their vested interest shows in our industryleading sales per employee  productivity thats almost twice the industry average many employees also own polaris machines and take our creed to heart understand the riding experience live the riding experience work to make it better roseau minnesota roseau near the canadian border is the birthplace of polaris and the sport of snowmobiling research development and manufacturing of atvs and snowmobiles are located in the roseau facility the  birth of polaris was the result of the dreams and aspirations of three exceptional men edgar hetteen david johnson and allan hetteen and the strength faith and ingenuity of a small community polaris roseau continues to promote innovative design and manufacturing techniques and industry leadership engineering product research development product testing and manufacturing of snowmobiles and atvs are the yearround activities of this facility a separate facility houses our stateoftheart plastic injection molding facility the molding facility supplies plastic parts for snowmobile and atv production in roseau and in spirit lake iowa roseau main plant th ave swroseau mn  wwwcityroseaumnuswwwwiktelcom medina minnesota just located west of minneapolis medina is our corporate headquarters which includes sales marketing service and administration the medina facility located in the twin cities houses sales marketing service technical training dealer support warranty finance and other administrative departments located on  wooded acres this facility provides the perfect atmosphere for introducing employees dealers distributors and customers to the way out experience corporate headquarters highway medina mn  wwwtwincitiescitysearchcomwwwamcitycomtwincitieswwwcbburnetcom wyoming minnesota wyoming minnesota is home to our new stateoftheart engineering facility the polaris product development center opened in wyoming minnesota in april  as a result of polaris outgrowing current facilities and the need to upgrade them to support our growth goals and provide the highquality polaris products our customers want highquality products start with highquality facilities and highquality people the facility is located approximately  miles north of minneapolisst paul minnesota and is  square feet the product development center is responsible for research and development of victory motorcycles allterrain vehicles atv ranger utility vehicles and polaris engines which includes prototype fabrication and assembly laboratories for structural testing electrical development materials engineering and powertrain assembly and dynamometer testing one unique characteristic of the facility is that it was built to achieve leed leadership in energy and environmental design certification the new facility may be the first in minnesota built using environmentally friendly standards created by the united states green building council leed standards aim to reduce or eliminate negative environmental or human impacts in five areas sustainable site planning safeguarding water and water efficiency energy efficiency and renewable energy conservation of materials and resources and indoor environmental quality wyoming development center east viking blvdwyoming mn   wwwchisagolakeschambercomwwwflaccorgwwwminneapolischamberorgwwwsaintpaulchambercomwwwwhitebearchambercomwwwcitydatacom spirit lake iowa our spirit lake facility manufactures select indian motorcycles and victory motorcycles polaris spirit lake is located in the northwest corner of iowa we are in the heart of the iowa great lakes where recreation and fun are a way of life the spirit lake facility was established in  and currently has  employees and  production lines these lines are dedicated to the final production of ranger and victory products this facility has  square feet located on  acres of land and has a welding department liquid and metal paint systems supporting our manufacturing operations spirit lake plant highway  spirit lake ia  wwwokobojicom osceola wisconsin osceola houses multiple engineering and manufacturing functions the osceola facility was established in  at that time the facility was a metal stamping operation with  employees working out of one building today the facility is considered a “drive train center of excellence” which includes power train design and engine assembly for all product lines it manufactures engines and supplies them to our final assembly sites in addition to specializing in engines osceola is home to gem product development for more information on osceola located in the scenic st croix river valley please visit the below links wwwpolkcountytourismcomwwwosceolakwiuswwwosceolamedicalcentercom huntsville plant in january  polaris announced plans to build a new production facility in huntsville ala to provide additional capacity and flexibility as the company continues to experience rapid growth located southwest of huntsville city center the  squarefoot facility will focus on polaris ranger offroad vehicle production and the slingshot motoroadster  polaris selected huntsville because it offers a skilled workforce existing utility infrastructure and a history of technology and innovation also huntsville offers strong local and state resources to support economic development the acre huntsville site allows polaris to be in close proximity to its key customer base in the southeast us thereby improving its logistics network huntsville is designed to be a lean and flexible facility driving continuous improvement from the start the new plant reduces complexity within the existing plant network and enables logistics optimization the facility has multiple assembly lines providing flexibility to quickly replenish demand and support continued product innovations equipped with stateoftheart technologies the plant will support several core processes including vehicle assembly metal fabrication welding chassis and body painting and injection molding at full capacity the site will employ  people the huntsville plant began production in q of    polaris industries inc  greenbrier parkway nw madison al  phone  wwwhsvchamberorg vermillion south dakota vermillion is our worldwide distribution center for parts and accessories to dealers around the world the vermillion distribution center was built in  as a result of rapid growth of the parts garments and accessories division of polaris industries inc when the need for space exceeded the capacity of three separate warehouse buildings in minnesota the decision was made to consolidate into one large facility away from 